 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Part-Time Educator (Online Programs) Cleary University 16 reviews United States Part-time Cleary University 16 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Part-time Full Job Description DESCRIPTION | QUALIFICATIONS: 
Cleary University seeks passionate and student-centered instructors who are highly engaging and intrinsically motivated to create meaningful, transformational, and dynamic learning experiences in the online learning environment. We need creative, innovative, and adaptable instructors who understand the level of technical engagement, personal investment, and technology-integrated approach needed to connect with our students in the online learning environment. Cleary is specifically looking for professionals who are tech savvy, possesses a high-level of self-assuredness, and are dedicated to playing a critical role in the personal, cognitive, and social growth of students. 
 We are currently seeking professionals with graduate degrees in the following disciplines:
 Analytics & Statistics 
Accounting & Finance 
Philosophy
 Business & Management
 Communication
 Economics 
Marketing
 Human Resource Management 
The  ideal candidate  is a people-centered, and engaging professional who: 
Continuously seeks opportunity for personal and professional growth
 Utilizes digital technology, video, podcasts, and multimedia to communicate with online students
 Utilizes digital technology, video, podcasts, and multimedia to enhance content and material in online courses 
Utilizes digital technology, video, podcasts, and multimedia to create active learning activities for online students
 Utilizes student-centered and active learning techniques to build long-lasting skill sets 
Is intrinsically motivated to personally connect with distance students
 Is highly engaging in technical and in-person environments 
Enjoys working collaboratively with other faculty members, departments, and staff to develop a meaningful experience for students 
Possesses natural people and communication skills
 Creatively implements methodology and activities that promote critical thinking, problem solving, and creativity
 Is enthusiastic about education for diverse, entrepreneurial-minded, global, multi-cultural students 
Required Qualifications : 
Able to communicate with students on a daily basis 
Create custom videos, podcasts, or other media on a weekly basis 
Provide additional resources and content knowledge on a weekly basis 
Digital communication skills and can utilize instructional technologies 
Highly engaging and passionate about education 
Out of the box, innovative, creative thinking skills 
Natural people and communication skills 
Minimum of a graduate degree or 18 graduate credit hours in the appropriate field is required
 **CMA or CPA preferred for accounting 
Prior teaching experience is preferred 
DUTIES | RESPONSIBILITIES 
Teaching : 
Utilize Canvas (LMS) engagement tools and video, digital communication, and content development features to deliver course content and maintain and record classroom attendance, grades, and assignments according to institutional standards 
Personally connect with students via video, voice, or in-person weekly 
Direct active, online classroom activities with students 
Utilize group work and online collaboration techniques to build student relationships and belonging 
Practice interactive pedagogical techniques to engage students and enhance the student experience in the online classroom 
Utilize the online calendar to regularly schedule office hours (minimum of 1 hour per week for each 3 credit hour course) and / or be available online to students on a regular basis 
Actively engage students in dialog and communication to form connections and build positive, lasting student/faculty/University relationships 
Assess student learning based on institutional outcomes, course goals and objectives in an unbiased, timely, and respectful manner 
Implement relevant, creative, and effective teaching methodologies to engage learners and inspire original thinking, problem solving, and entrepreneurial mindset 
Present course content through the filters of global sustainability, environment, AI/IT, communications, and ethics 
PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT |PROFESSIONALISM : 
Interact with student groups, campus administration, and faculty peers on regular basis 
Aspire to maintain a professional growth mindset and frequently seek opportunities to build scholarly and academic credentials, certifications, and experiences 
Purposely seek knowledge and practice in current and meaningful student engagement techniques, classroom management, student coaching, and evolving academic/learning needs and expectations Cleary University 30+ days ago original job If you require alternative methods of application or screening, you must approach the employer directly to request this as Indeed is not responsible for the employer's application process. Report job Apply Now Apply Now Save this job Save this job Educator jobs in United States Jobs at Cleary University in United States Educator salaries in United States Company Info Follow Get job updates from Cleary University Cleary University 16 reviews Cleary University is a Michigan-based business university with two campuses; the Washtenaw Campus is located in Ann Arbor and the Livings... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
 
